# EWP-001 — Implement PlatformApplication

**Engine:** VS08 – License, Subscription & Tenant Management Engine

**Milestone:** VS08A – Tenant Foundation

**Capability Contract:** CC-001 – PlatformApplication

**Status:** Approved for Implementation

---

# Objective

Implement the **PlatformApplication** aggregate exactly as defined by the approved CAP architecture.

This work package establishes the platform's catalog of business applications (e.g. Catering ERP, HSE, CRM, HRMS) and provides the foundation upon which application packages, installations, licensing, and marketplace capabilities will be built.

This work package implements **only the PlatformApplication aggregate**.

---

# Inputs

The implementation must comply with the following approved documents:

* ES-001 Database Standards

* ES-008 Architecture & Domain Modeling Standard

* ES-009 Data Ownership & Persistence Standard

* ES-010 Platform Naming & Namespace Standard

* ADR-008-001 through ADR-008-011

* DDS-101A Database Design Specification

* CC-001 PlatformApplication

---

# Scope

Implement the complete PlatformApplication aggregate including:

## Domain

* PlatformApplication aggregate root
* Domain validation
* Lifecycle rules

## Persistence

* Prisma model
* Database migration
* Repository interface
* Repository implementation

## Application Layer

Implement the following capabilities:

* Register Platform Application
* Update Platform Application Metadata
* Retire Platform Application
* Get Platform Application by Code
* Get Platform Application by Id
* List Platform Applications
* Search Platform Applications
* Filter by Category
* Filter by Status

## Validation

Implement validation for:

* Unique Application Code
* Unique Application Name
* Required fields
* Lifecycle transitions

## Testing

Implement:

* Unit tests
* Repository tests
* Integration tests

---

# Explicit Exclusions

Do **NOT** implement:

* PlatformApplicationPackage
* Platform Registry service
* WorkspaceInstallation
* Tenant
* TenantWorkspace
* Membership
* Licensing
* Subscription
* Billing
* Marketplace
* Runtime Integration
* Authorization Rules
* Publish Pipeline
* Manifest Generation

If additional functionality appears necessary, document it under **Deferred Items** rather than implementing it.

---

# Domain Rules

The implementation must enforce the following rules:

* Application Code is immutable.
* Application Code is globally unique.
* Application Name is globally unique.
* Display metadata may be updated.
* Retired applications cannot be modified except by approved lifecycle operations.
* PlatformApplication never references Tenant or Workspace.
* PlatformApplication never contains licensing information.
* PlatformApplication never contains installation information.

---

# Lifecycle

Supported lifecycle:

* Draft
* Published
* Deprecated
* Retired

Lifecycle validation must be centralized within the domain layer.

---

# Audit Requirements

Implement standard CAP audit support:

* CreatedBy
* CreatedOn
* ModifiedBy
* ModifiedOn
* DeletedBy
* DeletedOn
* IsDeleted

Hard delete is not permitted.

---

# Repository Requirements

Implement repository operations for:

* Create
* Update Metadata
* Retire
* Get By Id
* Get By Code
* List
* Search
* Exists By Code
* Exists By Name

Repositories must contain persistence logic only.

Business validation belongs in the service/domain layer.

---

# Service Requirements

Implement an application service that coordinates:

* Validation
* Lifecycle enforcement
* Repository interaction

The service must not contain persistence details.

---

# Database Requirements

Implement:

* Prisma model
* Migration
* Unique constraints
* Required indexes
* Soft delete support

Do not introduce tables outside the approved scope.

---

# Testing Requirements

Minimum coverage:

* Domain validation
* Repository operations
* Service operations
* Duplicate code validation
* Duplicate name validation
* Lifecycle transitions
* Soft delete behavior
* Search operations

All tests must pass.

